    "comment": "LIBERO-PRO (arXiv:2510.03827): the perturbed/robustness eval variant of LIBERO on the same single Franka Panda (robosuite/MuJoCo), 10 Hz. The observation/action INTERFACE is IDENTICAL to standard LIBERO (envs/libero.json) -- same robot_type, cameras, eef-pose+gripper state (8) and OSC EE-delta action (7), same per-quantity 'order' split and env-native names; no env-side normalization (dtype+stats only). What differs is ONLY the eval-time distribution: LIBERO-PRO reuses the standard LIBERO tasks but applies object swap/move/remove, initial-position, instruction (paraphrase/corruption), and environment (texture/lighting/camera) perturbations at rollout to probe whether a LIBERO-finetuned checkpoint memorized vs generalized. Training is identical to standard LIBERO, so the SAME LIBERO-finetuned checkpoints are evaluated here with no finetuning. stats/limits are carried over from standard LIBERO (physical-intelligence/libero); OPEN: perturbations can push observations outside these observed ranges -- treat stats as the standard-LIBERO distribution, not a bound. The free-running counterpart is envs/libero_pro_realtime.json."
}
